<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="&quot;IMAGE_20&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"ORI_IMG"</data>
  <data key="d1">"The image displays a clear, stylized white wheelchair accessibility symbol set against a solid black background. The symbol, commonly known as the International Symbol of Access, features a white outline of a person seated in a wheelchair. The person's head is represented by a small white circle, and their body is depicted with a 'V' shape for the torso and arms, with bent legs extending downwards. The wheelchair itself is shown with two large, spoked wheels on either side of the seated figure and a smaller front wheel, all rendered in white outline. The lines of the symbol are crisp and distinct, contrasting sharply with the deep black background, making it highly visible and recognizable. The overall impression is one of a standard, functional icon."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_20.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WHEELCHAIR SYMBOL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A white graphic symbol depicting a person seated in a wheelchair, which is the International Symbol of Access, indicating accessibility. It is set against a dark background."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_20.jpg</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BACKGROUND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d1">"A solid dark or black background providing high contrast for the white wheelchair symbol."</data>
  <data key="d2">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_20.jpg</data>
</node>
<edge source="&quot;IMAGE_20&quot;" target="&quot;WHEELCHAIR SYMBOL&quot;">
  <data key="d3">10.0</data>
  <data key="d4">"Wheelchair Symbol是从image_20中提取的实体。"</data>
  <data key="d5">C:/MMGraphRAG/MMGraphRAG/test_runs/api_working\images\image_20.jpg</data>
  <data key="d6">1</data>
